message: update version to 0.2.0, readme, and changelog
updated README and added config file example
removed unused imports and commented code, fixed metadata generation

Revert "removed useless DataFetcher class"

This reverts commit 925d86ec95c28ed01be416ccb02f60e509ccc862.
Fix typo and leftovers from merge conflict

added readme snippets as tests to make sure it's always up to date with
the latest release
add url encoding on sql query. String escaping when handling (triple quoted) query string multiple times is very brittle. url encoding solves this issue.
fno spec compliant, with remote GREL functions
Add Oracle JDBC driver via classpath
readme: add remark about duplicate removal and serialization format
README: add new features of Web of Things
README: document Private Security Data files

README: fix Markdown rendering and links

Docs are now at https://javadoc.io/doc/be.ugent.rml/rmlmapper

Main: add CLI option to run mapper in strict mode.

- In strict mode, the mapper will fail when it cannot convert a record to an IRI-safe triple.
Main: change short CLI option for strict mode to -strict

Main: remove `-strict` shorthand for strict mode

Only --strict will be accepted. Also added null safety to Main.checkOptionPresence for options that have no short version

Main: add argument to explicitly set Base IRI for generated terms

(R2)RML spec requires an executing environment variable to dictate the Base IRI, not the @base directive of the mapping file. The Main.main method now only uses the @base directive as base for generated terms when no explicit base IRI is set in the CLI, and strict mode is not enabled.

HTMLRecordFactory: add CSS3 selector support

Support CSS3 selectors as reference formulation.

CSVRecordFactory: Add spreadsheet support

Add XLSX and ODS file formats for reading spreadsheets as CSV files.

README.md: clarify that the releases contains complete jars

As discussed in issue 174

README: add RML Questions repo

We collect all questions now at https://github.com/kg-construct/rml-questions

RELEASE: update notes for releasing new versions

- Docker images need to be generated and pushed.
- Deployment to Maven Central must be done as well.
- Alpine Linux Merge Requests instructions.

README: add quick start guide

Make it clear for people how to easily start using the RMLMapper.

README: add quick start guide

Make it clear for people how to easily start using the RMLMapper.

functions_idlab.ttl, aaabim_java_mapping.ttl, pom.xml, README.md: FnO implementation mappings have class fno:Mapping instead of fnoi:Mapping, so changed all occurrences and updated `function-agent-java` and `grel-functions-java` to the newest versions which also fix his issue.

tests: refactor RDB tests to use Docker
